description:
Joss's life sucks. She's worried about exams and student loan debt when she'd much rather be watching the zombie movies she loves. So it's no surprise that when she tells her roommates that she's been attacked by a swarm of real-life, brain-hungering zombies-zombies!- they think the stress has finally cracked her.

But Joss knows she's sane- and it's a good thing, too! Because the zombies are real, and the she's the only one who knows how to fight them. Armed with "The Rules," truths about fighting the undead gleaned from zombie movies, Joss, Sonnet and Robyn just might make it out of their dorm alive.
name: OGN

person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: This Digital Exclusive collects OVER 150 PAGES of out-of-this-world content! Take a ride in a flying saucer with Cosmo the Merry Martian! For the first time ever, this classic interplanetary tale has been collected into one giant-size collection. Join Cosmo, Orbi, Astra, and all their wacky friends as they explore the unknown and discover all-new life forms. What adventures will these Martian explorers find on Jupiter, or Venus, or even Earth?! Put on your spacesuit and find out!
name: TPB

volume.name: Cosmo the Merry Martian: The Complete Series

description:
Presenting the full run of original A REAL AMERICAN HERO and SPECIAL MISSIONS tales, placed in proper reading order and collected in handsome hardcover volumes. Presiding over this project is legendary pop culture aficionado Mark W. Bellomo.

Collects G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero #1-12.
name: Volume 1

description:
Batman’s world has been devastated by his war against Talia, but is he willing to give up on his own humanity?

Note: The previous solicit does not hold. This issue was written by Chris Burnham and features a self-contained story with the Batman of Japan.
name: Interlude: A Bird in the Hand

description: It’s the final battle against the First Lantern and the Guardians in this, the extra-sized finale of Geoff Johns’ historic run on the title! Plus, don’t miss a special retrospective on Geoff’s run on GL!
name: The End

description: Can the Talon escape the jaws of death? What will become of him if he doesn’t? Find out in this story that leads directly into next month’s BIRDS OF PREY #21!
name: Don't be Afraid of the Dark

description: As the Scavenger compiles more Atlantean weaponry and artifacts, Aquaman enlists the aid of The Others to help find one missing relic in the Southwestern United States before his enemies can get to it. The issue also introduces a new member of the Others!
name: Skinwalker

description: The PROLOGUE TO TRINITY WAR continues as a revelation about Batman could destroy Wonder Woman and Superman’s relationship! Plus, in the backup story, the penultimate chapter of the tale of Shazam finds Billy Batson learning the shocking secret of Black Adam!
name: Prologue to Trinity War, Chapter Two: Secrets; Shazam! Chapter 12

description: It’s the penultimate chapter of the definitive Mad Hatter story—and not everyone makes it out alive!
name: Down, Down, Down

description: The Flash and Swamp Thing guest-star as the team struggles to recover the stolen House of Mystery from Dr. Destiny!
name: Horror City, Part 2: The Nightmare Gospel

description:
FIRST ISSUE SPECTACULAR!

Meet the ultimate slacker superhero for the 21st Century! Jasper Jenkins is a super-head AND a super-hero! He's relatable AND reliable and he's embarking on the adventure of a lifetime! The sensational debut of the new feel-good hero of the decade! You can't afford to miss it!

description: There are a million stories in Saturn City, and Simon Cooke's is just one of them! His future may be wide open, but the past is hot on his tail! The Old Man can still get it up! No two ways about it -- this is the perfect time to pay for SEX! It's even better than you think!

description: Ibrahaim's first door-to-door inspection goes badly when he's sent to the Holt farm. The Check brothers have Cooper hostage, and unfortunately for them, it's Em Cypress to the rescue.
The future collides with the past in this issue as Booster Gold causes problems for Jonah Hex. And in the backup story, a never before seen Stormwatch team takes the spotlight!

description: “WRATH OF THE FIRST LANTERN” epilogue! As a White Lantern, Kyle played a crucial role in the battle against the First Lantern and the Guardians. But a loss they suffered in the battle has left Kyle devastated, throwing off the control he had over the entire emotional spectrum. Has his time as a White Lantern ended before it’s truly begun? Find out in the conclusion of Tony Bedard’s run!
name: Reunion

description: “WRATH OF THE FIRST LANTERN” epilogue! Following the battle against the First Lantern and the Guardians, for the first time in centuries Atrocitus feels peace. What could possibly calm his legendary rage? And more importantly, what does that mean for the Red Lanterns? A surprising turning point for Atrocitus and the Red Lanterns in this, the conclusion of Peter Milligan’s run!
name: A Death Long Coming…

description: Hector Hammond is looking for Superman to save him from the New God known as Orion in “Metropolis Burning!”
name: Wham!

description: “Light and Dark” continues as the fallout of last issue’s attack threatens to drag the team into darkness!
name: Only Begotten

description: Hawkman vs. Blockbuster round two! Hawkman transforms his Nth metal armor into a new berserker mode! Blockbuster’s true identity is revealed! Plus, don’t miss an appearance by the new JLA!
name: The Deep!

description: An all-new Flash epic begins here, and the stakes have never been higher as Barry races toward a confrontation with the Reverse Flash!
name: Reverse, Part 1

description: Overwhelmed and beaten by a crew of Super-Villains, Ronnie and Jason are about to find out how bad things can get when Firestorm is labeled a living weapon of mass destruction and slated for dissection!
name: Problems Multiplied, Part Three

volume.name: The Fury of Firestorm: The Nuclear Man

description: Deathstroke’s origin revealed! You do not want to miss this! Plus: The Arrow pairs up with a familiar face to stop a madman with a Robin Hood complex, and when Oliver and Diggle get carjacked, they’re forced to take down the criminals using unconventional means.

description: In “Batman Beyond,” Terry squares off against the sinister Shriek, while Max uncovers the shocking truth about Undercloud. Plus: The Justice League continues the search for Kai-Ro, and you won’t believe who’s coming to the rescue in “Superman Beyond”!

description: The Incredible Hulk heads up our "monstrous heroes" issue! In addition to examining everybody's favorite enormous green rage monster (where you'll also find an in-depth interview with Herb Trimpe, the Hulk artist of the '70s) Comic Heroes takes a look at Deathlok and where he came from, built around an exclusive interview with creator Rich Buckler; there'll be a piece on Marvel's version of Dracula; and Hellboy, Fin Fang Foom, Zombo, Venom, the Demon, Frankenstein's monster, Concrete, and more!

In the conclusion to “Orpheus In the Underworld,” Tom meets the King of Hell again—and this time it’s even more unpleasant than before. The only way out is up, and the only way to get there is through a story. But what if the story says you have to lose? This issue leads directly into the epic fiftieth issue, and the start of THE UNWRITTEN FABLES!

From the brilliant imagination of video game auteur American McGee comes a dazzling reenvisioning of Red Riding Hood set in the wondrous world of Japanese folklore! Justin Aclin and Vasilis Lolos take Kani a young woman torn between two cultures on an epic adventure battling devious yokai for the fate of her world!

Based on the hot new game by American McGee’s Spicy Horse Games!

Step into the darkness with the brand-new Dark Horse superhero Blackout, written by Frank Barbiere with art by Micah Kaneshiro! Get ready for sci-fi action with the return of Ron Randall’s Trekker! Take the case and save the world with Donny Cates and Eliot Rahal’s Hunter Quaid! Paul Barry’s obsession with the ocean took a turn when his crew’s vessel was lost in a deep sea descent mission—with his crew inside. Fifty-five years later, with the recovery of the ship, Paul is about to discover the horrific mysteries of time and the abyss. From the pages of Dark Horse Presents.

But with the zombielike Numbers hounding their steps, they must make some unusual choices to avoid capture in an unknown world, with troubling consequences. description:
Je’daii Daegen Lok is on the verge of launching a war against the Je’daii. With the Force-strong stranger Xesh as his ally and a young Je’daii captive, Lok is close to his goal.

But Je’daii Rangers are close behind, as the Masters at the Temples have unlocked some of the secrets of Xesh’s origins. Something worse than the prisoner of Bogan is loose in the Tython system!

The Demon Knights learn of the twisted love shared by Madame Xanadu and Etrigan. Even more twists abound as they travel to Avalon to revive Merlin, only to find more dangers than they could have expected!

Spider-Woman & Kitty Pryde (with Lockheed in tow, of course) investigate some unfinished alien business!

Deadpool and Hawkeye do not see eye-to-eye!

description:
"CHILDREN OF THE SUN"

A day in the life of the Avengers...in the Savage Land.

The boys go hunting for dinosaurs and end up catching something else entirely.

Hyperion and Captain Universe begin the godlike education of the transformed Savage Land children.
name: Evolve

description:
Deadpool targets a MAN with AQUATIC powers!

Then he teams-up with your SUPERIOR Neighborhood SPIDER-MAN!

I PROMISE HE KILLS ONE OF THOSE TWO!

Synopsis

Deadpool and Benjamin Franklin travel down a road in a stolen ice cream truck. Benjamin is appalled and furious that Deadpool just killed their friend Michael the Necromancer. Deadpool explains that he was thinking outside the box and Benjamin leaves and floats into a strip club.

In Hell, Michael awaits his turn in a very long line. Too impatient, Michael calls to a demon in charge and asks to see Mephisto. The demon refuses but Michael insists that he has a secret Mephisto will certainly want to know. Michael gets eaten by the demon.

Back in Manhattan, Deadpool scales a building to get to his next target, a clairvoyant named Daniel Gump. Agent Preston tries to get Deadpool to rethink his actions but he explains that he knows what he is doing. He calmly walks into Gump's floor but gets immediately ejected. He is saved by Spider-Man (Doctor Octopus) and the two ascend the building. They meet Gump's troupe of protection and begin fighting.

Gump himself arrives with explosives strapped to his chest and a horde of mercenaries. Spider-Man webs Gump's hand and the two combat the mercs: Batroc, Chance, Lady Stilt Man, and Paste Pot Pete (er, the Trapster). Deadpool gets the upperhand by flooding the rooftop with the Trapster's paste, sticking most of the combatants to the roof (including Spider-Man). Deadpool steals Spider-Man's webshooters and pursues Lady Stilt Man, who has made off with Gump.

Gump sees Deadpool coming and gets a premonition as to what is about to happen. Before he can tell Deadpool's plan to Lady Stilt Man, however, Deadpool uses a webshooter to seal Gump's mouth. Deadpool then dispatches Lady Stilt Man by using explosives on her legs. He then kills Gump. Spider-Man shows up and knocks Deadpool out for being a murderer. Spider-Man hangs Deadpool up with the other mercs to await the arrival of the police. Deadpool finds a blowtorch, however, and is soon free.
name: Eight Legs to Kick You

description:
One day a year, The Thing reverts to his human form. This year... Ben Grimm is going to go home again -- as Ben Grimm!

What was Yancy Street REALLY like back in the day? And how long until the ever-loving' THING makes his appearance?

And meanwhile, the tables get turned in Franklin and Val's relationship... and when these two siblings have a rivalry, all bets are off.

description:
In a world where some villains became heroes instead Warrior Woman teams up with...Caroline LeFay?

The connection between the Fearless Defenders greatest foe and Morgan LeFay is finally revealed!

(And it's true in our world too!)
Micheline. Layton. Two voices that defined Iron Man come together to tell the untold story of his most dire hour - Armor Wars 2!

description:
HE'S BACK, BABY!

BETA RAY BILL RETURNS!

After her most recent (mis?)adventures, Sif's working on getting her, let's just call them feelings...under control.

However, when a certain hammer-wielding, space-faring ex shows up...all bets are off!

SPIDER-MAN VS. HULK VS. ZZZAX!

Kang and the The Apocalypse Twins enter the Age of Ultron, but what do they want?

Havok and Rogue, leaders of the Morlocks, must fight to save the man who condemned their people!
